==English==
===Alternative spellings===
* [[nocht]] (''Scottish'')
* [[nowt]]

===Etymology===
From Old English ''[[nōwiht]]''

===Noun===
'''nought'''
# A [[nothing]]; something which does not [[exist]].
# A thing or person of no [[worth]] or [[value]]; [[nil]].
# Not any [[quantity]] of [[number]]; [[zero]]; the score of no [[point]]s in a game.
# The [[figure]] or [[character]] presenting zero.

===Adjective===
'''nought'''
# Good for nothing; [[worthless]].
# [[wicked|Wicked]], [[immoral]].
# Zero.

===Verb===
{{en-infl-reg-consonant|nought||}}
# {{transitive}} To [[disregard]]; to [[despise]].
# {{intransitive}} To [[efface]] (oneself).

===Adverb===
'''nought'''
# To no [[extent]]; in no way; [[not at all]].
# [[not|Not]].

===Pronoun===
'''nought'''
# Nothing; zero.

===Derived terms===
* [[noughty]]

===See also===
* [[naught]]
* [[ought]]

